<h1>Layouts</h1>

<p>
    Drop a <code>_layout.razor</code> file in any <code>Pages/</code> subfolder. Every page
    in that folder (and below) is wrapped by it automatically.
</p>

<h2>The shortest possible layout</h2>
<pre><code>&lt;nav&gt;...&lt;/nav&gt;
&lt;main&gt;
    @@Body
&lt;/main&gt;</code></pre>

<p>
    You don't write <code>@@inherits LayoutComponentBase</code> — the
    <code>AspNext.Runtime.targets</code> MSBuild target injects it on first build (idempotent).
    If you'd rather a different base class, write <code>@@inherits MyBase</code> up-front and
    the auto-injection becomes a noop.
</p>

<h2>Nesting</h2>
<p>Layouts compose — each <code>_layout.razor</code> in an ancestor directory wraps the next:</p>
<pre><code>Pages/_layout.razor                ← root (nav, footer)
Pages/Blog/_layout.razor           ← blog-specific shell (e.g. categories bar)
Pages/Blog/[slug].razor            ← page renders inside Blog layout, inside root layout
Pages/Counter.razor                ← only the root layout</code></pre>

<p>
    The generator detects the chain by walking from the page's directory upward and emits a
    <code>[Layout(typeof(OuterLayout))]</code> attribute on each inner layout's partial.
    Blazor follows the chain at render time.
</p>

<h2>Cascading <code>[Authorize]</code></h2>
<p>
    Add <code>@@attribute [Authorize]</code> to a layout — the generator copies the attribute
    onto every page beneath it. The whole subtree is protected with one line.
</p>
<pre><code>@@* Pages/Dashboard/_layout.razor *@@
@@attribute [Authorize]

&lt;aside&gt;...sidebar...&lt;/aside&gt;
@@Body</code></pre>

<p>
    Parameterized variants work too: <code>@@attribute [Authorize(Roles="admin")]</code> or
    <code>@@attribute [Authorize(Policy="adults-only")]</code>.
</p>

<h2>Explicit override</h2>
<p>
    Want to use a layout that lives somewhere other than the conventional
    <code>_layout.razor</code>? Use the magic comment:
</p>
<pre><code>@@* @@nxt:layout=MyApp.Some.OtherLayout *@@</code></pre>

<p>The explicit form takes precedence over auto-detection.</p>
